The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Sify loss down to $7 m

 Chennai, April 19 (PTI): Sify Ltd, a leading Internet, network and e-commerce services provider, has pared down its net loss to $7.05 million for the year ended March 31 compared with $8.51 million in the previous fiscal.

 Revenues increased 29 per cent to $82.8 million in the last fiscal. 

 If the profit on sale of businesses were to be excluded, the net loss for the reporting year would have been 37 per cent lower than the previous year, the company said in a statement.

 Cash profit for the year was $5.17 million compared with $1.93 million registered in the previous year.

 Sify ended the year with a cash balance of over $31 million after incurring a capital expenditure of $11.4 million and licence entry fee of $2.3 million for IP-VPN.

 ?During the year, we have invested to strengthen our capabilities to aggressively grow the enterprise business, broadband services, portal and international businesses. These investments have resulted in an expanded network across 99 cities and a broader customer base across both the business consumer segments,? said R. Ramaraj, managing director and CEO.

 During the year, corporate services of the company accounted for 56 per cent of revenues and retail Internet access business accounted for 39 per cent. 




